---
import ClaudeCodeLayout from "../../layouts/ClaudeCodeLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<ClaudeCodeLayout
  title="Claude Code Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes | changelogs.info"
  description="Get Claude Code installed and running in 10 minutes. Anthropic's terminal-native AI coding agent."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">🧠</div>
      <h1 class="cc-headline cs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="cs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Up and running in 10 minutes — terminal-native AI coding agent that understands your codebase.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="cc-headline cs-panel__title">Prerequisites</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Node.js 18+</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Required runtime. Check with <code>node --version</code></p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Get your API key from <code>console.anthropic.com</code>. Export it in your shell profile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cc-headline cs-panel__title">Install</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Install globally via npm</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cc-headline cs-panel__title">First Run</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">1. Navigate to your project</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> cd your-project</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">2. Launch Claude Code</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> claude</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Opens the interactive TUI. Claude reads your repo structure automatically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="cc-headline cs-panel__title">First Real Task</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Understand your codebase instantly</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd cs-item__cmd--accent"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> claude "explain this codebase in 3 sentences and list the main entry points"</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">This is the fastest way to validate that Claude Code is working and reading your project correctly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="cc-headline cs-panel__title">What Next?</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Try headless mode</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> claude --print "summarise this" &lt; file.txt</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Use <code>--print</code> mode for scripting and CI integration.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Add a CLAUDE.md</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Create a CLAUDE.md in your repo root with build commands, conventions, and constraints. Claude reads it automatically.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Explore permission modes</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">For trusted repos, bypass approval prompts entirely.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/claude-code/cheatsheet/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Cheatsheet →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">All the commands and workflows at a glance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/claude-code/tips/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Tips & Tricks →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Quick wins, hidden features, and common mistakes to avoid.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <a href="/claude-code/changelog/" class="cs-item__title" style="color: var(--tool-primary-bright); text-decoration: none;">Changelog →</a>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Stay up to date with every release.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</ClaudeCodeLayout>
